      "orig": "Separex membrane systems are used primarily for bulk CO 2 removal from natural gas streams. The systems are modular, skid mounted units containing either spiral wound or hollow fiber membrane elements. The elements are housed in pressure tubes in various configurations depending on system requirements.",
      "text": "Separex membrane systems are used primarily for bulk CO 2 removal from natural gas streams. The systems are modular, skid mounted units containing either spiral wound or hollow fiber membrane elements. The elements are housed in pressure tubes in various configurations depending on system requirements."
