      ],
      "orig": "/L50189 Enhanced Oil Recovery (EOR) Operations -Separex membrane systems are used to recover carbon dioxide from EOR floods for recycle injection.  Systems can be used as a baseload system, designed as part of the recovery plant, or as a debottlenecking unit upstream of the existing recovery plant.",
      "text": "/L50189 Enhanced Oil Recovery (EOR) Operations -Separex membrane systems are used to recover carbon dioxide from EOR floods for recycle injection.  Systems can be used as a baseload system, designed as part of the recovery plant, or as a debottlenecking unit upstream of the existing recovery plant.",
      "enumerated": false,
      "marker": ""
    },
